]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="fl-builder-content fl-builder-content-10044 fl-builder-content-primary fl-builder-global-templates-locked" data-post-id="10044"><div class="fl-row fl-row-fixed-width fl-row-bg-none fl-node-ru2y0v4gkm8c fl-row-default-height fl-row-align-center" data-node="ru2y0v4gkm8c">
	<div class="fl-row-content-wrap">
						<div class="fl-row-content fl-row-fixed-width fl-node-content">
		
<div class="fl-col-group fl-node-cj20meavk9yl" data-node="cj20meavk9yl">
			<div class="fl-col fl-node-mwb7k0eoifqr fl-col-bg-color" data-node="mwb7k0eoifqr">
	<div class="fl-col-content fl-node-content"><div class="fl-module fl-module-rich-text fl-node-woqa015r8xy2" data-node="woqa015r8xy2">
	<div class="fl-module-content fl-node-content">
		<div class="fl-rich-text">
	<p>Press Release<br />
Date: March 1, 2024</p>
<h2>New Leadership at CM Hammar AB, Starting April 1, 2024</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH.jpg"><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-10047 alignleft" src="https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="486" height="486" srcset="https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-64x64.jpg 64w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-600x600.jpg 600w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH-100x100.jpg 100w, https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MattiasM_AnnaH.jpg 1662w" sizes="(max-width: 486px) 100vw, 486px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Gothenburg, Sweden - CM Hammar AB, a world leader in maritime safety, announces the appointment of Mattias Malmgren as CEO partnering a co-leadership model with Anna Hultberg as COO, effective April 1, 2024. This leadership change marks a strategic move to further strengthen the company’s ability to operate in the international market, with a continued focus on the manufacturing of life-saving products in Sweden.</strong></p>
<p>Mattias Malmgren, who previously held the position of Head of Marketing and Sales at CM Hammar, will continue to focus on external relations and strategic partnerships in his new role. Anna Hultberg, formerly the CFO and Sustainability Manager, will take charge of the company’s internal operations and relations. Together, their complementary skills represent a strategic investment towards enhancing the company’s global market presence and are expected to drive further innovation and sustainability initiatives.</p>
<p>The departing CEO, Håkan Skutberg, will transition to a new role within the Ernström Group as Business Area Manager for Global Niche Products, overseeing CM Hammar along with other market leader companies within their nische.</p>
<p><em>“I am fully confident that Mattias and Anna will successfully lead CM Hammar, ensuring the company continues to be a significant part of the business area and the Ernström Group. They have both played a crucial role in getting the company to where it is today, and I am convinced they will continue to develop our successful business model with a strong focus on customers, employees, and sustainability,”</em> says Håkan Skutberg.</p>
<p>CM Hammar is a leading actor in the field of sea safety, specializing in delivering high-quality products and solutions to ensure safety at sea. With a strong emphasis on innovation and customer satisfaction, CM Hammar continues to be a reliable partner for customers around the world.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
